{"id":20858,"title":"Infections in liver transplant recipients.","abstract":"Liver transplant is a life-saving procedure for many end-stage liver diseases. Despite measures such as the use of protective barriers, antimicrobial prophylaxis, and vaccination, infections still represent a major cause of morbidity and mortality after liver transplant. This article reviews major infectious concerns after liver transplant. ","date":"2014-03-18","categories":"Bacterial Infections and Mycoses","split":"test","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24635787","annotations":[{"name":"Liver transplantation","weight":0.822325,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Liver_transplantation"},{"name":"Vaccination","weight":0.809223,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vaccination"},{"name":"Death","weight":0.803478,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Death"},{"name":"Disease","weight":0.797998,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disease"},{"name":"Prophylaxis","weight":0.765655,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prophylaxis"},{"name":"Liver","weight":0.746246,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Liver"},{"name":"Organ transplantation","weight":0.72904,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Organ_transplantation"},{"name":"Morbidity","weight":0.725335,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Morbidity"},{"name":"Infection","weight":0.695621,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Infection"},{"name":"Antimicrobial","weight":0.555578,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Antimicrobial"},{"name":"Surgery","weight":0.329215,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Surgery"},{"name":"Antimicrobial prophylaxis","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Antimicrobial_prophylaxis"}]}
